# basis
## introduction
%%visits: 5
A basis is the combination of span linear independence

We require that solving solutions to [[differential_equation]]s and similarly [[recurrence_relation]]s requires us to try a basis of possible solutions.

## intuition
A basis is in a sense a coordinate system. Allows component wise things

We need the basis to be linearly independent so that there is only one way to represent a vector with our basis
## rigour
$e_1,e_2,e_3$ are the standard basis $\begin{pmatrix} 1 \\ 0 \\ 0 \end{pmatrix},\begin{pmatrix} 0 \\ 1 \\ 0 \end{pmatrix},\begin{pmatrix} 0 \\ 0 \\ 1 \end{pmatrix}$ 
